article.description: N. Dakota St. 68, UC Santa Barbara 60
article.headline: N. Dakota St. 68, UC Santa Barbara 60
article.linkText: N. Dakota St. 68, UC Santa Barbara 60
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. -- Michael Tveidt scored 18 points and Taylor Braun added 12 points as North Dakota State beat UC Santa Barbara 68-60 on Saturday night in the BTI Invitational. Eric Carlson added 11 points and nine rebounds for the Bison (1-1). After being held scoreless in the first half, Carlson scored five consecutive points to give North Dakota State its largest lead of the game, 55-35, with 10:29 remaining. Orlando Johnson scored a game-high 30 points for the Gauchos (1-1). Johnson, the Big West player of the year last season, made a 3-pointer and converted a three-point play to bring UC Santa Barbara within 62-56 with 1:28 remaining. But North Dakota State, which went 11-18 last season, answered with a 5-0 run to secure the win. Both teams conclude the three-day BTI Invitational on Sunday.
